Bridges the gap between mid-century modern / 1960s lounge styles and the 1980s Art Deco revival 'Deco-Luxe' style and the 'Contempo-Eclectic' style. Common materials include: glass, mirrored glass, steel, brass, lucite/acrylic, gold, silver, granite, marble, plush carpeting, velvet, leather. Tiered forms, angled surfaces, prismatic effects, simple geometric shapes in various compositions, dramatic and even somewhat disorienting spaces. Usually paired with plush, comfortable furniture.

Short for 'Geometric-Glamorous', this is the mid 1970s - mid 1980s luxurious materials + geometric forms design aesthetic, sometimes referred to as cocaine decor. Bridges the gap between mid-century modern / 1960s lounge styles and the 1980s Art Deco revival 'Deco-Luxe' style and the 'Contempo-Eclectic' style. It can be considered a sub-aesthetic or tied to Late-Modern architecture. Common materials include: glass, mirrored glass, steel, brass, lucite/acrylic, gold, silver, granite, marble, plush carpeting, velvet, leather. Tiered forms, angled surfaces, prismatic effects, simple geometric shapes in various compositions, dramatic and even somewhat disorienting spaces. Usually paired with plush, comfortable furniture.
